; Template for export_presets.cfg (which is git-ignored -- Godot writes
; keystore paths/passwords into that file in plain text as soon as you
; fill them into the export dialog, so it must never be committed).
;
; Copy this file to export_presets.cfg and adjust for your machine. Every
; keystore field below is intentionally blank: the debug preset falls
; back to the debug keystore configured in Editor Settings > Export >
; Android, and the release preset has no keystore at all until you point
; it at your own (see the README's "Android build" section) -- never put
; a real release keystore path/password here.
;
; Same principle for the iOS preset: application/app_store_team_id is
; required by Godot even for an unsigned, project-only export, but is
; left blank here on purpose -- fill in your own Team ID locally (see the
; README's "iOS build" section for how to find it). code_sign_identity_*/
; provisioning_profile_* are blank too, same "never commit signing
; secrets" rule.

